")        << indent() << "typelib_typedescription_release( pTD );
" << indent()        << "// End inline typedescription generation

" << indent()        << "return new ::css::uno::Type( " << getTypeClass(name_)        << ", pTypeName ); // leaked
";into the same method - which should also save re-looking up the type name via that string; so some:css::uno::Type *createAndRegisterType(..., const char *pName, ...);Of course, it's a C API - so prolly we want to return a reference and have a no-acquire constructor for the C++ wrapper around it (?)So - I think we can go further here to get more savings =)
